<a title="Free to Choose: A Personal Statement" href="http://www.goodreads.com/book/show/97820.Free_to_Choose">Free to Choose: A Personal Statement </a>by <a class="zem_slink" title="Milton Friedman" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Milton_Friedman" target="_blank" rel="wikipedia">Milton</a> and <a class="zem_slink" title="Rose Friedman" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rose_Friedman" target="_blank" rel="wikipedia">Rose Friedman</a>- Sometimes it is important to go back to the basics and appreciate the wonder of voluntary cooperation. Although markets are not perfect, the Friedman's lay out many examples illustrating the power of them. A great introduction to economic reasoning for the layman.</div>
